<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Arhu on 05-09-2002 11:27 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Ragon: ~[i]Best would be a voiceover in which the char makes a remark to "let the player know" about his status in this regard.
(Could be short sentences like "Oh thanks, i had my payload for today!" or "That´s just too far with my burden! Have to take my time...")[/i]~

Aye, that would be nice. Or let the character groan every once in a while when he is overloaded.

Dorien: First, welcome to this forum and I agree with Nem - very impressive post! Would have been worth an own topic if you ask me, but I guess it fits in here too. Lots of thoughts went into your letter, lots of consensual and continuing thoughts are drifting in my mind, but I've no time right now to elaborate.

Talking about the possibilities of object combinations, I agree with you that there could be more, and multiplayer has always been a very important point in our discussions. In fact, most if not all Larians would have liked to have MP support as well (you can read interviews at [URL=http://www.rpgdot.com]www.rpgdot.com[/URL]  ), but there are always two problems concerning such features: time and money. Larians started out as, and still is, a very small company, and they originally funded the project themselves by making gambling games at the same time. Considering that they were/are only so few people, it's astounding what they have managed to create.

Still.. if they are ever going to create an add-on... *wink, wink*

As for Morrowind, there's a nice post from someone talking about different aspects of the game, which kind of player would like it, and in that resembling your own impressions of multi player vs. single player: [URL=http://groups.google.com/groups?hl=de&safe=off&selm=oDFA8.852%24L22.684411062%40newssvr13.news.prodigy.com&rnum=1]Link[/URL].

[i]Meow...[/i]
Arhu</TEXTAREA>
